

patching ,
apply tags ✔ Affects new machines created after the change
❌ Does NOT update existing Azure VMs

- name: Discover and patch MachineSets
  hosts: localhost
  gather_facts: no
  collections:
    - kubernetes.core

  vars:
    namespace: openshift-machine-api

  tasks:

    - name: Get all MachineSets
      kubernetes.core.k8s_info:
        api_version: machine.openshift.io/v1beta1
        kind: MachineSet
        namespace: "{{ namespace }}"
      register: machinesets

    - name: Patch MachineSet tags
      kubernetes.core.k8s:
        state: present
        api_version: machine.openshift.io/v1beta1
        kind: MachineSet
        name: "{{ item.metadata.name }}"
        namespace: "{{ namespace }}"
        merge_type: merge
        definition:
          spec:
            template:
              spec:
                providerSpec:
                  value:
                    tags:
                      to_intake: "{{ to_intake | string }}"
                      mapid: "{{ mapid | string }}"
                      transit: "{{ transit | string }}"
      loop: "{{ machinesets.resources }}"
	  
	  
	  
Important Behavior in OpenShift

Updating MachineSet tags:

✔ Affects new machines created after the change
❌ Does NOT update existing Azure VMs

to verify
oc get machineset <machineset_name> -n openshift-machine-api -o yaml | grep -A5 tags



